Package: cat.web
Title: Web Content Classification with LLMs
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Chris", "Soria", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "chrissoria@berkeley.edu")
Description: R interface to the Python catweb package. Classifies, extracts,
    explores, and summarizes web content (URLs or text) using LLMs. A thin
    domain wrapper around cat.stack that adds automatic URL fetching and
    web-context prompt injection (source domain, content type, metadata).
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Imports:
    reticulate (>= 1.28),
    cat.stack (>= 0.1.0)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
